<h1>From C. W. F. Dumas</h1>
<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Lahaie 24<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> Avr. 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Notre bon Ami, Mr. De Gyzelaar, en vous prsentant ses complimens, me charge de vous demander vos meilleures recomandations pour un home de Lettres, dont il fait grand cas, Mr. Boinod, Suisse, qui a lev les Enfans de Mr. Gevaers, excellent Patriote, nom &amp; lu depuis peu Bourguematre  Dort. Mr. Boinod se propose de partir dans peu pour Philadelphie, avec un Associ &amp; un Garon Relieur, &amp; dy tablir une Librairie franoise. Mr. le Duc de la Vauguyon a remis en partant une Lettre en sa faveur  Mr. le Chev. De la Luzerne. Il sera pareillement recomand  Mr. Van Berckel; &amp; Mr. De Gyzelaer lui a fait esprer, que V. Exc<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> voudra de son cot accrditer son entreprise.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>Vous verrez, Monsieur, dans lincluse, ce qui sest pass entre Mr. Fagel &amp; moi.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>Il y aura Samedi 26 un grand festin  Amsterdam,  lhonneur de Mr. De Capelle du Pol &amp; de Mr. Van Berckel le Pensionaire. Mr. son frere &amp; Mr. De Gyzelaer sy trouveront aussi; &amp; le Buste de Barneveld, dit-on, y prsidera.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> Le Lundi suivant Mr. Van Berckel &amp; sa future se feront inscrire, cest--dire marier  la Maison de Ville, &amp; quinze jours aprs ils seront bnis, &amp;c.</p>
<p>Jacob nest pas encore arriv.</p>
<p>Je suis avec grand respect, De Votre Exc<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> / le trs-humble &amp; trsobis- / sant serviteur</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0440">[440<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0440.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
<div class="translation">
<h2><span class="hi-all-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps; text-transform: lowercase;">Translation</span></h2>
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 24 April 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Our good friend Mr. Gyselaar presents his compliments and asks you to provide your best recommendation for a man of letters whom he values highly: Mr. Boinod, a Swiss gentleman who was tutor to the children of Mr. Gevaers, an excellent patriot, recently elected Burgomaster of Dordrecht. Mr. Boinod intends to leave shortly for Philadelphia, together with a colleague and a bookbinder, and start a French bookstore there. In parting, the Duc de La Vauguyon sent a letter on his behalf to the Chevalier de La Luzerne. He will be similarly recommended to Mr. Van Berckel, while Mr. Gyselaar has given him cause to hope that your excellency too will lend credence to his enterprise.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></p>
<p>The enclosed letter will show you what took place between Mr. Fagel and me.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>On Saturday the 26th there will be a grand banquet in Amsterdam in honor of Mr. Van der Capellen tot den Pol and Mr. Van Berckel the pensionary. Mr. Van Berckels brother and Mr. Gyselaar will be there tooand the bust of Oldenbarnevelt, they say, will preside.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> The following Monday Mr. Van Berckel and his intended will be registeredthat is to say, marriedat the town hall, and fifteen days later they will receive the nuptial blessing etc.</p>
<p>Jacob has not yet arrived.</p>
<p>I am with great respect, your excellencys very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-sn">
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); internal address: Paris  S. E. Mr. Adams M. P.</p>
</div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> recommended Boinod to Thomas Mifflin in a letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0284" class="document">28 April</a>, below, but see also the <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0223" class="document">16 March letter from Jacobus and Jan Anthony Murray</a>, and note 1, above.</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>Probably Dumas 18 April letter to Robert R. Livingston containing a 23 April postscript describing that mornings meeting with Fagel (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Revolutionary Diplomatic Correspondence of the United States&lt;/i&gt;, ed. Francis Wharton, Washington, 1889; 6 vols. ]">Wharton, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 6:383384). As described, the meeting was very much in line with Dumas intentions as expressed in the final paragraph of his <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0270" class="document">22 April letter</a>, above.</p>
</div>
        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0271-fn-0003">3</a>
   <p>For <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s comments on the Dutch statesman and martyred immortal Patriot Johan van Oldenbarnevelt, see vol. <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0100#ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0177" class="pageNo">10:177</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0190#ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0354" class="pageNo">354</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0190%20ADMS-print-06-10-02-0191#ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0355" class="pageNo">355</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-10-02-0251%20ADMS-print-06-10-02-0252#ADMS-06-10-02-pb-0438" class="pageNo">438</a>.</p>
</div>
